IRS990.MissionDesc: CULTIVATE. EDUCATE. CELEBRATE. WE GROW OUR COMMUNITY BY CONNECTING PEOPLE, PLANTS, AND NATURE.
IRS990.Desc: HORTICULTURE: OPERATED A BOTANICAL GARDEN OPEN TO THE GENERAL PUBLIC. PROVIDED OPPORTUNITY FOR THE PUBLIC TO VIEW AND LEARN ABOUT A WIDE VARIETY OF FLOWERS, PLANTS, ORNAMENTAL SHRUBS, AND TREES THAT THRIVE IN THE INTERMOUNTAIN REGION. GARDEN FACILITIES AND DISPLAYS PROMOTE SUSTAINABILITY AND CELEBRATE THE RICH CULTURAL CONNECTIONS BETWEEN PEOPLE AND PLANTS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: VISITOR SERVICES: WELCOMED AND ORIENTED VISITORS AND PROMOTED A POSITIVE VISITOR EXPERIENCE, PROVIDING VISITORS WITH CULTURAL EXPERIENCES FEATURING MUSIC, PAINTING AND SCULPTURE, CULINARY ARTS AND MORE IN A GARDEN SETTING. MANAGED VISITOR AMENITIES AND COORDINATED PUBLIC USAGE OF FACILITIES BY LARGER GROUPS FOR FUNCTIONS AND EVENTS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: EDUCATION: PROVIDED PROGRAMS, INITIATIVES, AND WORKSHOPS TO CHILDREN AND ADULTS AND A RICH ARRAY OF OPPORTUNITIES IN HORTICULTURAL AND ENVIRONMENTAL EDUCATION. EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMS ADVANCE A MISSION OF SUSTAINABILITY AND DEMONSTRATE OUR COMMITMENT TO EDUCATING STUDENTS AND THE GENERAL PUBLIC ABOUT ENVIRONMENTAL STEWARDSHIP SPECIFIC TO IDAHO AND THE INTERMOUNTAIN REGION AND ACROSS THE GLOBE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ACCOUNTING STANDARD ON ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES ADDRESSES THE DETERMINATION OF WHETHER TAX BENEFITS CLAIMED OR EXPECTED TO BE CLAIMED ON A TAX RETURN SHOULD BE RECORDED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. UNDER THAT GUIDANCE, THE ORGANIZATION MAY RECOGNIZE TAX BENEFIT FROM AN UNCERTAIN TAX POSITION ONLY IF IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THAT THE TAX POSITION WILL BE SUSTAINED ON EXAMINATION BY TAXING AUTHORITIES BASED ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION. THE TAX BENEFITS RECOGNIZED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS FROM SUCH A POSITION ARE MEASURED BASED ON THE LARGEST BENEFIT THAT HAS A GREATER THAN 50 PERCENT LIKELIHOOD OF BEING REALIZED UPON ULTIMATE SETTLEMENT. THERE WERE NO UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS IDENTIFIED OR RECORDED AS LIABILITIES FOR FISCAL YEARS 2023 AND 2022 THE ORGANIZATION FILES FORM 990 IN THE U.S. FEDERAL JURISDICTION. THE ORGANIZATION IS GENERALLY NO LONGER SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE FOR YEARS BEFORE 2019.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 1A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNING BODY OF THE ORGANIZATION DELEGATES BROAD AUTHORITY TO THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE TO ACT ON ITS BEHALF DURING INTERVALS BETWEEN MEETINGS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE IS EMPOWERED PER THE BYLAWS TO TRANSACT BUSINESS FOR THE ORGANIZATION SUBJECT TO THE REVIEW, APPROVAL AND RATIFICATION OF THE BOARD. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE IS COMPRISED OF THE OFFICERS OF THE ORGANIZATION AND THE IMMEDIATE PAST PRESIDENT AS VOTING MEMBERS AND THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AS A NON-VOTING MEMBER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS ELECTRONICALLY DISTRIBUTED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS FOR REVIEW PRIOR TO FILING. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE REVIEWS THE DOCUMENT AND REQUESTS COMMENTS FROM BOARD MEMBERS. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE PRESENTS AND MAKES A RECOMMENDATION TO THE FULL BOARD AND THE BOARD VOTES TO APPROVE OR DISAPPROVE THE RETURN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION REGULARLY AND CONSISTENTLY MONITORS COMPLIANCE WITH THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY. AN ANNUAL QUESTIONNAIRE IS FILLED OUT BY OFFICERS, BOARD MEMBERS, KEY EMPLOYEES, AND DIRECTORS. INFORMATION IS REVIEWED AND MEMBERS WITH A CONFLICT OF INTEREST ARE REQUESTED TO ABSTAIN FROM VOTING ON THAT SPECIFIC MATTER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND KEY BOARD MEMBERS CREATE A BUDGET FOR COMPENSATION. COMPENSATION IS COMPARED TO THAT OF OTHER SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS NATIONALLY; SEVERAL BOARD MEMBERS ARE MEMBERS OF OTHER LOCAL NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATIONS AND DISCUSSION OF LOCAL COMPENSATION CAN FACTOR INTO THE BUDGET AS WELL. THE BUDGET IS PREPARED BY THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, REVIEWED BY THE FINANCE COMMITTEE WITH RECOMMENDED APPROVAL, AND THEN SENT TO THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE FOR FINAL BOARD APPROVAL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICIES AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST AT THE MAIN OFFICE DURING NORMAL BUSINESS HOURS.
NO CHANGE IN THE OVERSIGHT PROCESS OR SELECTION PROCESS DURING THE CURRENT TAX YEAR.
